.TH JEKYLL\-SERVE "User Manual"
.SH NAME:
.PP
jekyll serve
.SH DESCRIPTION:
.PP
Serve your site locally and make sure it is awesome
.SH SYNTAX:
.PP
jekyll serve [options]
.SH COMMANDS:
.TP
\fB\fC--config CONFIG_FILE[,CONFIG_FILE2,...]\fR
Custom configuration file
.TP
\fB\fC--future\fR
Publishes posts with a future date
.TP
\fB\fC--limit_posts MAX_POSTS\fR
Limits the number of posts to parse and publish
.TP
\fB\fC-w\fR, \fB\fC--watch\fR
Watch for changes and rebuild
.TP
\fB\fC--lsi\fR
Use LSI for improved related posts
.TP
\fB\fC-B\fR, \fB\fC--detach\fR
Run the server in the background (detach)
.TP
\fB\fC-D\fR, \fB\fC--drafts\fR
Render posts in the _drafts folder
.TP
\fB\fC-v\fR, \fB\fC--verbose\fR
Print verbose output.
.TP
\fB\fC-P\fR, \fB\fC--port [PORT]\fR
Port to listen on
.TP
\fB\fC-H\fR, \fB\fC--host [HOST]\fR
Host to bind to
.TP
\fB\fC-b\fR, \fB\fC--baseurl [URL]\fR 
Base URL
.SH ALIAS:
.PP
server